From 6a0137101f47301fff2da6ba4b9048383d569909 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Sep 2020 10:06:23 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: Intel: bytcr_rt5640: Add quirk for MPMAN Converter9 2-in-1
Git-commit: 6a0137101f47301fff2da6ba4b9048383d569909
Patch-mainline: v5.9-rc6
References: jsc#SLE-16518

The MPMAN Converter9 2-in-1 almost fully works with out default settings.
The only problem is that it has only 1 speaker so any sounds only playing
on the right channel get lost.

Add a quirk for this model using the default settings + MONO_SPEAKER.

Signed-off-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Pierre-Louis Bossart <pierre-louis.bossart@linux.intel.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20200901080623.4987-1-hdegoede@redhat.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/intel/boards/bytcr_rt5640.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/boards/bytcr_rt5640.c b/sound/soc/intel/boards/bytcr_rt5640.c
index 479992f4e97a..fc202747ba83 100644
--- a/sound/soc/intel/boards/bytcr_rt5640.c
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/boards/bytcr_rt5640.c
@@ -591,6 +591,16 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id byt_rt5640_quirk_table[] = {
 					BYT_RT5640_SSP0_AIF1 |
 					BYT_RT5640_MCLK_EN),
 	},
+	{	/* MPMAN Converter 9, similar hw as the I.T.Works TW891 2-in-1 */
+		.matches = {
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "MPMAN"),
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "Converter9"),
+		},
+		.driver_data = (void *)(BYTCR_INPUT_DEFAULTS |
+					BYT_RT5640_MONO_SPEAKER |
+					BYT_RT5640_SSP0_AIF1 |
+					BYT_RT5640_MCLK_EN),
+	},
 	{
 		/* MPMAN MPWIN895CL */
 		.matches = {
